## Public Member Functions

### getAddressSpace() {#a967d4e2e2313363b16a669d715813d0c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>virtual uint32&#95;t llvm::AAAddressSpace::getAddressSpace () const</>}>
Return the address space of the associated value.

<code>NoAddressSpace</code> is returned if the associated value is dead. This functions is not supposed to be called if the <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aa">AA</a> is invalid.
